cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper discusses a novel decision-based attack algorithm for image recognition systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of deep neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the vulnerability of image recognition systems to adversarial examples, which could place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of adversarial perturbations and the optimization of the attack algorithm suggest that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
